pve-storage-ontap-nvmetcp (1.0-6) stable; urgency=medium

  * fix: remove discard=unmap and detect-zeroes=unmap from
    qemu_blockdev_options. PVE rejects these options against its
    allowed schema, generating 4 warnings per VM start. The plugin
    must only return backend access (driver + filename); discard is
    managed by qemu-server from VM disk configuration (discard=on).
    The automatic TRIM feature from 1.0-3 was silently dropped by
    PVE and never effective.

 -- Nicolas I. (McKay1717) <https://github.com/McKay1717>  Thu, 20 Mar 2026 12:00:00 +0100

pve-storage-ontap-nvmetcp (1.0-5) stable; urgency=medium

  * feat: add cloud-init disk support (vm-<vmid>-cloudinit). Fixes #1.
    Cloud-init disks use a different naming convention than regular
    disks. Five functions now handle the cloudinit pattern:
    parse_volname, _parse_ontap_disk_name, _ontap_to_pve,
    alloc_image, and list_images.
    Reported-by: PandemiK911

 -- Nicolas I. (McKay1717) <https://github.com/McKay1717>  Thu, 20 Mar 2026 10:00:00 +0100

pve-storage-ontap-nvmetcp (1.0-4) stable; urgency=medium

  * fix: declare 'shared' option to enable live migration.
    PVE migration framework refused to migrate VMs with disks on ONTAP
    NVMe/TCP storage ("storage type 'ontapnvme' not supported") because
    the plugin did not declare 'shared' in options(). PVE ignored the
    'shared 1' directive in storage.cfg and treated the storage as
    node-local.
  * feat: force shared=1 by default in plugindata(). ONTAP NVMe/TCP
    storage is inherently shared — all cluster nodes connect to the
    same namespaces via NVMe-oF/TCP fabric. Admin can still restrict
    access per-node with 'nodes' property.

 -- Nicolas I. (McKay1717) <https://github.com/McKay1717>  Thu, 13 Mar 2026 17:00:00 +0100

pve-storage-ontap-nvmetcp (1.0-3) stable; urgency=high

  * fix: ONTAP REST API pagination — follow _links.next across all
    paginated responses. list_images was limited to 20 records,
    causing volumes to be invisible when SVM had >20 objects.
  * fix: implement clone_image (full clone via dd between NVMe devices)
    and restore volume_has_feature('copy') to enable VM cloning.
  * fix: untaint NVMe device paths for Perl taint mode (pvedaemon -T).
    Paths from nvme-cli JSON, sysfs, and config were tainted, causing
    "Insecure dependency in exec" errors during clone/qemu-img operations.
  * fix: untaint NVMe/TCP portal addresses from ONTAP API and config.
  * fix: ONTAP version requirement 9.18+ → 9.10.1+ in control.in
    and Api.pm (9.18 does not exist).
  * fix: missing \n on die in on_add_hook error path.
  * fix: URI escaping on vol_name, cg_name, subsystem_name in API
    query strings — prevents malformed HTTP requests with special
    characters in storage_prefix.
  * fix: removed unused imports (get_standard_option, trim).
  * feat: force discard=unmap and detect-zeroes=unmap at QEMU
    blockdev layer — automatic thin reclaim on ONTAP.
  * feat: verify_ssl property — TLS certificate verification for
    ONTAP management connections (default: off).
  * feat: debug property — configurable debug logging (0/1/2)
    output to syslog via pvedaemon journal.
  * doc: added SECURITY.md, GitHub issue templates.

 -- Nicolas I. (McKay1717) <https://github.com/McKay1717>  Sun, 22 Feb 2026 12:00:00 +0100
